<br />
Well, one class can solo mid to high level PvP encounters (see paladin), and if you put two paladins together its very difficult, not impossible, but damn difficult to beat. If a level 15 is dumb enough to involve themselves in combat they arent ready for, they deserve to die. This is why I like the PvE servers, because you cant openly gank lowbies unless they are put into that situation by killing a PvP-active NPC, or physically engaging in combat against a PvP-active player, both of which are purely voluntary. Or their dumb and put up the PvP flag via /pvp, either way their asking for a beat down by anyone not on their team. Even in medevil days, you still had kids and such running buckets of stone to the garrisons, or squires taking armour / weapons for the knights. They never participated in combat directly, but they helped indirectly. You didnt see a seperate field for all the squires and children who were part of the opposing villages duking it out individually while the adults fought though. They were all on the same field of play.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
