Extremely good point from an immersion standpoint.  I love the fact that they built a mechanim into the PvP for lower level players.  It makes High End less of an elitism situation if you ask me.  Balances the usefulness of a full range of players in any guild.  You will actually NEED people willing to do the side quests etc available to low ends, and I know if I was a lvl 60 I would not appreciate being relegated to completeing a quest designed for a lvl 30 while the rest of my guild was off doing the "fun and challenging" part of the battle.  I believe this way actually makes continuity for guilds in constantly raising low level players into the tactics for raids much more effective.  No longer will it be necessary as it is in EQ to put level/AA limits on your new recruits....</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
